---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/common/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/common/Footer.astro';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  const posts = [
    {
      slug: 'ai-marketing-2026',
      title: 'AI Marketing in 2026: What to Expect',
      excerpt: 'Discover the latest trends in AI marketing and how they can transform your strategy.',
      date: '2026-02-15',
      category: 'AI & Automation',
      readTime: '5 min',
      content: `
## The Rise of AI Marketing

Artificial Intelligence is no longer just a buzzword—it's fundamentally changing how we approach marketing. In 2026, AI marketing has evolved from experimental to essential.

### Key Trends for 2026

1. **AI Agents** - Autonomous marketing agents that handle optimization, bidding, and content creation
2. **Hyper-Personalization** - Real-time content customization based on user behavior
3. **Predictive Analytics** - AI that forecasts customer behavior before it happens

### What This Means for Your Business

The companies embracing AI marketing today are seeing:
- 40% improvement in campaign ROAS
- 50% reduction in customer acquisition costs
- 3x faster time-to-market for new campaigns

### Getting Started

You don't need to replace your entire marketing stack. Start with:
1. AI-powered bidding in your PPC campaigns
2. Automated content personalization
3. Predictive lead scoring

The future of marketing is AI-first. Are you ready?
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: 'tiktok-ads-guide',
      title: 'TikTok Ads Guide for 2026',
      excerpt: 'Learn how to effectively use TikTok ads for your business growth.',
      date: '2026-02-10',
      category: 'PPC & Advertising',
      readTime: '7 min',
      content: `
## TikTok Ads: The Complete Guide for 2026

TikTok has evolved from a Gen Z platform to a serious marketing channel. Here's everything you need to know.

### Why TikTok Matters in 2026

- 1B+ monthly active users
- Highest engagement rates of any platform
- Spark Ads revolutionized influencer marketing

### Campaign Types

1. **In-Feed Ads** - Appear in the For You feed
2. **Spark Ads** - Boost organic content with paid promotion
3. **TopView** - Premium placement at the top of the app
4. **Brand Takeovers** - Full-screen ads when app opens

### Best Practices

- Keep videos under 15 seconds for maximum completion
- Use trending sounds and hashtags
- Partner with creators for authentic content
- Test Spark Ads for best ROI

Ready to launch your first TikTok campaign?
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: 'seo-ai-search',
      title: 'SEO for AI Search: ChatGPT, Perplexity',
      excerpt: 'How to optimize your website for the new era of AI search.',
      date: '2026-02-05',
      category: 'SEO',
      readTime: '6 min',
      content: `
## The New Frontier: AI Search Optimization

With AI Overviews, ChatGPT, and Perplexity changing how people find information, traditional SEO is evolving rapidly.

### What's Different About AI Search?

- Answers are generated, not just found
- Citations and sources matter more than ever
- Long-tail conversational queries are rising

### How to Optimize for AI Search

1. **Structured Data** - Use schema markup for better AI understanding
2. **E-E-A-T Signals** - Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, Trustworthiness
3. **Conversational Content** - Write as people actually ask questions
4. **Cite Your Sources** - Make it easy for AI to reference your content

### The Future is Now

Companies optimizing for AI search now are seeing:
- Higher visibility in AI Overviews
- More qualified traffic from AI referrals
- Better brand mention tracking

Start optimizing for AI search today.
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: 'marketing-automation-roi',
      title: 'Marketing Automation ROI: Real Results',
      excerpt: 'Case study: How we achieved 312% ROI through marketing automation.',
      date: '2026-01-28',
      category: 'Case Studies',
      readTime: '8 min',
      content: `
## Case Study: 312% ROI with Marketing Automation

A B2B SaaS company came to us struggling with lead quality and conversion rates. Here's how we fixed it.

### The Challenge

- Low lead quality from inbound marketing
- Manual follow-up process taking 48+ hours
- 2% conversion rate on landing pages

### Our Solution

1. **Implemented HubSpot** for marketing automation
2. **Created 12 automated nurture sequences**
3. **Set up lead scoring** based on engagement
4. **Integrated CRM** for seamless sales handoff

### The Results

| Metric | Before | After |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Conversion Rate | 2% | 6.5% |
| Lead Response Time | 48 hours | 5 minutes |
| Marketing Qualified Leads | 50/month | 180/month |
| ROI | - | **312%** |

### Key Takeaways

- Automation isn't about replacing humans—it's about scaling what works
- Lead scoring prevents wasted sales time
- Personalization at scale is possible with the right tools

Ready to see similar results?
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: 'ppc-trends-2026',
      title: 'PPC Trends You Need to Know in 2026',
      excerpt: 'From AI-powered bidding to privacy-first targeting.',
      date: '2026-01-20',
      category: 'PPC',
      readTime: '6 min',
      content: `
## PPC in 2026: The Complete Guide

The PPC landscape has changed dramatically. Here's what you need to know to stay competitive.

### Major Trends

1. **AI-Powered Bidding** - Smart Bidding now handles 80% of optimization
2. **Privacy-First Targeting** - First-party data is your most valuable asset
3. **Cross-Platform Attribution** - Track customers across Google, Meta, TikTok

### Platform Updates

**Google Ads:**
- Performance Max gets AI upgrades
- Demand Gen campaigns expand
- AI Overviews affect search behavior

**Meta Ads:**
- Advantage+ shopping campaigns are now standard
- Live Audio Rooms for brand building
- Improved conversion API

### What Works in 2026

- Creative testing at scale
- Audience segmentation based on behavior
- Integration of organic + paid content

Stay ahead of the curve.
      `,
    },
    {
      slug: 'klaviyo-automation',
      title: 'Klaviyo Automation Best Practices',
      excerpt: 'Master Klaviyo automation flows to increase revenue.',
      date: '2026-01-15',
      category: 'Email Marketing',
      readTime: '5 min',
      content: `
## Klaviyo Automation: Maximum Revenue Guide

Email marketing automation is one of the highest-ROI marketing activities. Here's how to make it work.

### Essential Automations

1. **Welcome Series** - Set the tone for customer relationships
2. **Browse Abandonment** - Capture interest before it fades
3. **Cart Abandonment** - Recover lost revenue (average 15% recovery rate)
4. **Post-Purchase** - Drive repeat purchases and reviews
5. **Win-Back** - Re-engage dormant customers

### Klaviyo Best Practices

- Use custom properties for personalization
- A/B test subject lines and send times
- Segment by engagement level
- Integrate with your CRM for unified data

### The Numbers

- Email marketing generates $36 for every $1 spent
- Automated emails have 70% higher open rates
- Cart abandonment emails recover 15% of lost revenue

Start building your automations today.
      `,
    },
  ];

  return posts.map((post) => ({
    params: { slug: post.slug },
    props: { post },
  }));
}

const { post } = Astro.props;
---

<Layout
  title={`${post.title} - Blog`}
  description={post.excerpt}
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <main class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <article class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-3xl">
      <!-- Back link -->
      <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 mb-8 hover:underline">
        ← Back to Blog
      </a>

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-primary-100 dark:bg-primary-900/30 text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300">
            {post.category}
          </span>
          <span>{post.readTime} read</span>
          <span>·</span>
          <span>{new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</span>
        </div>
        
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
          {post.title}
        </h1>
        
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
          {post.excerpt}
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <Fragment set:html={post.content.replace(/\n/g, '<br/>').replace(/## (.+)/g, '<h2>$1</h2>').replace(/### (.+)/g, '<h3>$1</h3>').replace(/\*\*(.+?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>').replace(/\*(.+?)\*/g, '<em>$1</em>').replace(/- (.+)/g, '<li>$1</li>').replace(/\|(.+)\|/g, (match) => {
          const cells = match.split('|').filter(c => c.trim());
          return '<tr>' + cells.map(c => `<td>${c.trim()}</td>`).join('') + '</tr>';
        })} />
      </div>

      <!-- Share -->
      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-dark-700">
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
          Share this article:
        </p>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <a href={`https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://marketing.tvoje.info/blog/${post.slug}`} target="_blank" class="btn-secondary px-4 py-2">
            LinkedIn
          </a>
          <a href={`https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=${encodeURIComponent(post.title)}&url=https://marketing.tvoje.info/blog/${post.slug}`} target="_blank" class="btn-secondary px-4 py-2">
            Twitter
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="mt-12 p-8 rounded-2xl bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
          Ready to implement these strategies?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
          Let's discuss how we can help your business grow.
        </p>
        <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">
          Get in Touch
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>
